MRF-map,reduce,filter

Syntax

Uses 

sample Example programs to use MRF 

Copy By value and Reference

Task:MRF on rest countries api


Map:
1.will be applicable to array
2.will take function as a parameter
3.it will be applied to each and every element of the array
4. it will return a new array

syntax:
arrayname.map(function);

function consit of ele as a main parameter
ele-> array elements


result:its a new array

exceptions:

1.map will have an error if no function is passed 

typeerror

2.suppose if return is missing , then it will throw undefined 

array of undefined


ex:
var student=[{name:'alex',marks:60},{name:'bob',marks:70}];
console.log(student.name)
using above array increase the marks of the students by 10
using map function


Filter:
1.will be applicable to array
2.will take function as a parameter
3.it will be applied to each and every element of the array
4.if a condition inside an array get passed , it will be pushed to new array or else it will be ignored...



syntax:
arrayname.filter(function);

function consit of ele as a main parameter
ele-> array elements


1.filter will have an error if no function is passed 

typeerror

2.suppose if return is missing , then it will throw undefined 

array of undefined


Ex: 
var student=[{name:'alex',marks:60},{name:'bob',marks:70},{name:'alice',marks:80}];print the names  of the students whose marks greater than 60

Expected Output:
var res=[bob,alice];




Reduce:will reduce the entire array into single values
syntax:
arrayname.reduce(function);

function consit of acc,ele
acc,ele as a parameter

acc:initial value
acc:accumulator
ele/item:array element


s1:if acc is not defined 
acc will take first index value as a parameter


s2:if acc is  defined 
acc will take initalized value



let arr=[12,14,65.5,87];
sum of the array 


